text: Added the textures for grass blocks and stone.
Added the textures for cobblestone, dirt and planks, and a unique side texture for the grass block.
Changed textures of grass block and stone.
Added textures for bedrock, water and lava. The water and lava textures would be used until 0.0.19a, at which point they would be used as placeholder textures (see placeholder textures section).
Changed textures of lava and oak saplings.
Added textures for coal ore, iron ore, gold ore, sand, gravel, the sides and top/bottom of logs, and leaves.
Changed the textures of cobblestone and planks.
The textures of sand, gravel, logs and leaves have changed.
The textures for glass and sponges have been added.
Updated the glass texture, once again.
Added textures for sixteen cloth colors, the block of gold, dandelions, roses, red mushrooms and brown mushrooms.
Added textures for the block of iron, bricks, bookshelf, mossy cobblestone, smooth stone slab and TNT, and reworked the block of gold to use three textures instead of one.
Changed the colors of the gray cloth variants and tnt.
Added textures for chests and their large counterparts.
Added the textures for diamond ore and the block of diamond.
The textures used for the gear are not found in terrain.png, but rather in the /misc folder.
Added textures for the crafting table.
Added textures for farmland and wheat crop blocks.
Added textures for ladders and doors (doors at this point used distinct textures for left and right).
A new texture has been added for leaves, specifically for fast graphics.
The ladder and door textures have been darkened.
Removed all of the cloth textures, except for white. Also removed were the right-hinge door textures - doors now use a flipped left hinge for right hinge doors instead.
The spawner texture has been added.
Added the textures for redstone ore, redstone torches, redstone wire, levers and iron doors.
Added textures for ice, snow, and for snow-covered grass blocks.
The textures for cactus have been added.
Added the textures for clay and sugar cane.
Updated the bricks and cactus textures.
Added the textures for netherrack, soul sand, glowstone, pumpkins and jack o'lanterns.
Slight changes have been made to rail textures.
Grass block and leaves textures have been made grayscale in light of the new biome coloring system.
Added textures for dispensers, spruce leaves, birch logs, spruce logs, lapis lazuli blocks, sandstone, cakes and fifteen new wool colors.
Added textures for redstone repeaters and beds.
Redstone wire is now colored via a tint system, resulting in two new redstone wire textures being added and the original two removed.
Added textures for birch saplings, spruce saplings, powered rails, detector rails and a tintable side texture for grass blocks.
The unused cobweb texture has been changed, and cobwebs actually implemented.
An invisible overlay texture for redstone wire has been added, its exact purpose unknown.
Added textures for dead bushes, grass, ferns and trapdoors.
Added textures for pistons, including a back texture which duplicates that of the furnace and dispenser.
Updated the bricks and cobblestone textures.
The way in which textures are applied to blocks has been improved to eliminate odd inconsistencies. As a result, the textures for cakes and beds have changed.
Added textures for stone bricks, cracked stone bricks, mossy stone bricks, red mushroom blocks, brown mushroom blocks, mushroom stems, melons, iron bars, glass panes, vines and stems.
Changed the texture of mossy cobblestone.
Added textures for lily pads, mycelium, nether bricks and nether wart.
Added textures for brewing stands, enchanting tables and end portal frames.
The end portal frame's textures changed, and end stone implemented.
Changed the textures of blocks of diamond, gold, iron, bricks, dirt, glowstone, grass block tops, gravel, netherrack and planks.
Changed the textures of the sides of grass blocks and sand.
Added textures for jungle logs and jungle leaves.
Changed the dispenser and oak sapling textures.
Added birch planks, spruce planks, jungle planks, cut sandstone, chiseled sandstone and chiseled stone bricks.
Slightly changed the sandstone side texture and most wool colors.
Added emerald ore, with the incorrect texture.
Added textures for the block of emerald, tripwire and tripwire hook.
The texture of tripwire has been changed to be lighter or more translucent.
The textures of stems have changed slightly - their textures have been moved a pixel to the left.
Added the textures for beacons and command blocks.
Added textures for flower pots, carrots and potatoes.
Added redstone comparators, daylight detectors and nether quartz ore.
Added textures for block of quartz, chiseled quartz block, quartz pillar and activator rail. The top and side texture of usual quartz blocks are identical, but are distinct files.
Added unique hopper textures. The top and inside texture is one duplicates of the cauldron textures.
Added actual animated textures for water, lava, fire and nether portals.
Added textures for vertically facing dispensers and droppers.
Detector rails now have a unique texture for when activated.
Added the block of coal texture.
Changed the block of coal and lapis lazuli block textures.

Added alliums, azure bluets, blue orchids, oxeye daisy, orange tulips, pink tulips, red tulips, white tulips, lilacs, peony, rose bushes, sunflowers, tall grass, large ferns, packed ice and podzol along with their respective textures.
Roses have been effectively replaced by poppies.
Added red sand and its texture.
Added stained glass and stained glass panes.
The stained glass related textures have changed.
Added textures for the acacia log block, acacia saplings and dark oak saplings.
Added acacia planks and dark oak planks textures.
The acacia log texture has been updated, and a unique texture has been added for the dark oak log (it was previously identical to the spruce log).

Added unique top textures for each log type, which previously reused the oak log top texture. Individual texture files existed for each log type before this version, although were duplicates of the oak log top texture.
Added textures for granite, polished granite, diorite, polished diorite, andesite, polished andesite and slime blocks.
Added the texture for iron trapdoors.
Updated cauldron textures in accordance with its model change.
Hoppers now have a unique top texture.

The oak trapdoor texture file is now 442 bytes (previously 357). Whether this is due to any visual changes is unknown. Testing indicates no - the only changes appear to be to the transparent portions.
Added textures for the new prismarine, prismarine bricks, dark prismarine and sea lantern blocks.
Updated the sponge texture and added a texture for the new wet sponge.
Added a new texture for coarse dirt.
Removed the textures for fast leaves.
Added a texture for the daylight detector when inverted.
Added textures for red sandstone, cut red sandstone and chiseled red sandstone.
Added textures for five new door types.
The jungle door inside texture has been removed.
Added textures for beetroots, then-grass paths, chorus plants, chorus flowers, end rods, end stone bricks, purpur blocks, purpur pillars and structure blocks.
The textures used for redstone dust have changed - the dot now has its own texture, and two different line textures are used on it.
Added new textures for command blocks.
Changed the command block textures and added a specific texture for conditional command blocks.
Added textures for bone blocks, magma blocks, nether wart blocks and red nether bricks.
Added a unique texture for the observer's output when active.
Changed the top and front textures.
Added textures for sixteen colors each of concrete, concrete powder and glazed terracotta.
The textures of four glazed terracotta blocks have changed.
Removed the bed block textures - beds are now handled as entities.
Added textures for unique trapdoor variants.
Added textures for kelp, seagrass, dried kelp blocks, stripped logs and turtle eggs.
Added the textures for coral blocks.
Updated the textures of kelp and living coral blocks.
Added individualized dead coral block textures.
The generic dead coral block texture has been removed.
Added the textures for coral fans.
Added the texture for sea pickles.
Updated four of the five coral fan textures.
Added blue ice and its texture.
Changed water's texture to allow for more extensive biome tinting.
Removed the mirrored dried kelp block side texture.
Added unique textures for the tops of wood blocks.
Changed the stripped jungle log side texture.
Removed the wood block top textures.
Added textures for dead coral fans.
Added the textures for cornflowers, lily of the valley, wither roses, bamboo and looms.

Updated a large amount of textures. Many blocks which had identical textures are now visually distinct: oak, birch, acacia and dark oak leaves, unripe carrot, potato and beetroot crops, piston backs are now distinct from the furnace/dispenser/dropper texture, ice from intact frosted ice, the block of quartz's top texture differing from its side texture (by one pixel), and possibly more.
Added textures for barrels, bells, blast furnaces, cartography tables, fletching tables, grindstones, lecterns, smithing tables, smokers and stonecutters.
The enchanting table's bottom texture is now identical to that of obsidian from the previous snapshot.
Updated the lectern front and side textures, and the grindstone pivot texture.
The lectern top side, base side and bottom textures appear to have been removed.
Added textures for jigsaw blocks and lanterns.
Updated the textures of several of the new crafting stations.
Updated a good amount of textures.
Updated log and stripped log top textures, and spruce door and trapdoor textures, among others.
Added textures for the sweet berry bush.
Overhauled the campfire, removing its top and side textures and replacing them with log textures.
Added a dedicated texture for open barrels.
The block of quartz top and side textures have been changed. Both are now identical in texture, no longer differing by one pixel.
The loom top texture has flipped to fix MC-146295.
Updated the iron ore and crafting table textures.
Added textures for the newly added bee nests and beehives.
Added textures for honey blocks and honeycomb blocks.

Added ancient debris, basalt, crimson and warped wood products, roots, nether sprouts, the block of netherite, fungi, soul soil, shroomlights, weeping vines, soul fire, soul torches and soul lanterns.
Updated the nether wart block texture.
Added textures for crying obsidian, targets and potted roots.
Updated purpur pillar and stripped stem top textures.
Added textures for nether gold ore and twisting vines.
Added textures for polished basalt and respawn anchors.
Added a lock texture for the jigsaw block.
Updated the nether gold ore texture.
Added textures for blackstone and derivatives, cracked nether bricks, chiseled nether bricks, quartz bricks and soul campfires.
Updated two blocks from the previous snapshot.
Updated the back texture of the observer.
The textures of amethyst clusters, block of amethysts, budding amethyst, calcite, tuff, tinted glass, block of coppers, cut copper and 17 types of candle are added.
Updated several textures from the previous snapshot.
Added textures for dripstone blocks and pointed dripstone.
Updated the amethyst block textures once again.
Added the moss block, glow berries, big dripleaf, small dripleaf, spore blossom, azalea leaves, hanging roots, rooted dirt and azaleas textures.
Added stem textures to small dripleaf.
Added textures for deepslate, chiseled deepslate, deepslate bricks, polished deepslate and deepslate tiles.
Updated textures to gold ore, iron ore, redstone ore, coal ore, diamond ore, polished blackstone bricks, cracked polished blackstone bricks and side texture of blackstone.
Compressed textures of green concrete powder and fully grown nether wart.
Added deepslate ores, smooth basalt and cobbled deepslate textures.
Updated coal, copper, iron, gold, redstone, lapis lazuli and emerald ore, deepslate, chiseled deepslate, deepslate bricks, polished deepslate, deepslate tiles and side texture of blackstone.
Added deepslate variants of coal ore, copper ore, emerald ore, cracked deepslate bricks and cracked deepslate tiles textures.
Updated coal ore, iron ore, gold ore, diamond ore, deepslate, cobbled deepslate and all deepslate ores textures.
Updated gilded blackstone, snowy grass block, pumpkin and smoker textures.
Added raw iron, raw copper and raw gold blocks.
Updated gold ore, deepslate copper ore, lapis lazuli ore and deepslate lapis lazuli ore textures.
Changed Blocks of raw iron and gold textures.
Changed textures of Block of Raw Metals.
Added lit candles and potted azalea textures.
Changed redstone comparator on and cave vines plant textures.
Fixed and changed big amount of textures.
Changed dirt path and stripped dark oak log textures again.
Added reinforced deepslate, sculk, sculk catalyst, sculk shrieker and sculk veins textures.

Added all froglight types, frogspawn, mangrove leaves, mangrove log stripped mangrove log, mangrove planks, mangrove door, mangrove trapdoor, mangrove propagule, mangrove roots, muddy mangrove roots, mud, packed mud and mud bricks textures.
Updated and fixed brewing stand, cocoa (stage 2), end portal frame, end rod, mycelium side and smoker bottom textures.
Readded all sculk blocks textures into a regular snapshot.
Readded reinforced deepslate textures into a regular snapshot.
Added can summon sculk shrieker texture, it uses old inner top texture.
Updated sculk shrieker inner top texture, now it uses when sculk shrieker cannot summon a warden.
Changed side sculk shrieker and mangrove leaves textures.
Added the oak sign texture. While the sign was an entity in this version, this same exact texture would later go on to be used when the sign was reimplemented as a block in Infdev 0607.
Chests now use entity rendering and a new texture.
Added textures for chests during the Christmas event.
These textures were included as part of the first Texture Update resource pack, but did not appear in any actual Java Edition versions.
Several other textures recieved updated versions and some 1.0.0 textures were also updated. The textures shown here did not appear in Java Edition game versions either.
Added a specific texture for burnt-out torches.
Added textures for the USB Charger Block.
Added textures for an ant, box of infinite books, cursor and funky portal.
Added shulker box top textures, as the fix for MC-107383.
Updated the shulker box top textures, excluding purple.
Purple shulker boxes are now distinct from normal shulker boxes.

texts.text: This article is about all changes made to block textures. For the texture atlas that housed all block textures before Java Edition 1.5, see terrain.png.

This page attempts to document the full history of the textures of blocks, their additions, changes, and removals. Additions and changes made to the models of blocks and any new blocks that reuse prior textures will not be documented here. Texture files that are completely identical to other texture files will also be largely ignored for the time being.

1 List
1.1 Used block textures
1.1.1 Blocks which use entity rendering
1.2 Texture Update pre-releases
1.3 Joke version exclusive textures
1.4 Textures used for block particles
1.5 Placeholder textures
1.5.1 History
1.5.1.1 Missing textures
1.5.1.2 Block placeholder textures
1.5.1.3 Animation placeholder textures
2 Unused textures

Differences to investigate according to winmerge results (many may just be insignificant compression differences):
Enchanting table bottom texture changed in 18w44a and 18w50a
Acacia, birch, dark oak, jungle and oak trapdoors and the observer back and top changed between 17w47a and 1.13.2 (likely just compression)
List textures which are or were duplicates:
13w43a dark oak log was added named as big oak log, but with spruce logtexture
Whenever birch leaves got a unique texture
Original acacia and dark oak leaves
Melon vs pumpkin stem and their attached versions
Water overlay texture used for water against glass and co. MC-35790 implied a 15w43b introduction, MC-128276 a 18w22b change and 1.16-pre5's changelogs a darkening, but these all need confirmed.
These textures are also used for blocks. However, the blocks in question render as entities rather than blocks. As such, the textures they use are much more akin to entity textures.
These textures were released as one of the two Texture Update resource packs but have never appeared in a full version.

Note: this section only includes textures that are exclusive to the Texture Update preview resource packs. Unchanged textures from before which were included with the pack, as well as textures that went on to make it into the game officially, are not currently included.
These textures only existed in specific joke versions and never appeared in official releases.
These textures are not used directly for any blocks but are instead used for defining particles they emit upon being broken, fallen on, or sprinted on.
This section documents both placeholder textures for errors, and those formerly used for animated blocks.
